args:
In order to calm the angry Master of the Sea,
Patia, Mikoto and the imperial soldiers show
it how much fun they're having. With the dragon
satisfied, the beach saved, and karma earned,
the two can finally resume their vacation.
*pant* *pant* Blue seas... White sand...\nHuh. Maybe everything is okay afterâ€”
Bwa ha ha ha! Dance, you fools! Dance!\nFrolic until my fury is sated!
This is the very portrait of pandemonium.\nWhat are we to do?
You're asking me?!\nWell, we know force isn't an option\nsince you couldn't defeat it before.
But how else are you supposed to stop\na creature called the Master of the Sea?!
Ah geez, this is a real mess. Guess I\ngotta try that trick to appease the Master\nof the Sea my granny used to talk about...
Hold, friend! Say that again!\nThe part about the trick, I mean.
Guardians of the beach. Very important.\nNow cease your stammering and teach us\nhow to appease the Master of the Sea!
Uh, right! Okay. So my granny used to live\nhere a long time ago, and she told us\nabout this old local legend...

She said the Master of the Sea was easily
angered, and the only way to appease him
was to surf a great wave and pull off a
bunch of fancy tricks for its amusement.
A dubious story, but as we lack for other\noptions, I suppose it cannot hurt to try.
I've heard worse plans. Okay, Mikoto,\nyou ride the wave while I do volleyball\ntricks. Sound good? Great! Let's go!
Pray feast your eyes upon this impressive\ndisplay of our greatest talents.
What the...? That dude is riding a wave\nwhile throwing some lady in the air!

I have attained divine revelation;
I am now both man and wave.
I will ride that torrent to bring amusement
enough to soothe even your turbulent soul.
And I will be handling the fancy tricks.
Show me the way into that\ndragon's heart, mirageball!
I know this is just people hitting a ball\nand riding a wave, but I just... *sniff*\nIT'S SO BEAUTIFUL!
I can't imagine how anyone could be\nunmoved by such a spectacle.
Oh, come on! It hasn't even NOTICED!
Damn and damn again!\nWas the legend wrong?!
The path of reason is at its end.\nWe've no choice but to wager our lives\nand resort to the force of arms.

I can't believe I'm the one saying this,
but I don't think violence is the answer.
Heck, we humans are the ones who
angered it in the first place!
Yeah, this beach is supposed to be a\nplace for everyone to enjoy themselves!\nAin't that what you taught us?
The Master of the Sea just wants to be\nhappy. That's why it told us to dance:\nso it could be entertained!
Of course! Okay, right, let's try againâ€”\nwith all of us together this time.\nThat should be enough to reach it.
Heeeeyyy, Master of the Sea!\nCheck how hard we're groovin'\non these sick waves, brah!
There's so much love and peace and\nstone-cold groovy vibes on this beach!\nI've never HAD so much fun!
The humans are positively\nshimmering with joy...
Love really can save the world, dudes!\nWooooo! Party ooooon!
So if we just keep putting out good vibes,\nthe Master of the Sea will be appeased?
Perhapsâ€”but it is possible that simply\nenjoying ourselves will not be enough.
You yourself questioned why a dragon\nwould grant humans power, yes?
I can sense from the flow of energy\nemitted by the beast that it is a dragon\nwho is compelled to seek enjoyment.
It grants humans power to please them,\nthat it might share in their delight.

And this beach would be the perfect place
for that 'cause everyone is enjoying their
vacations together no matter their
races or previous allegiances!
Then it's settled. Everyone, I hereby order\nyou to enjoy the hell out of this beach!
We'll have so much fun that even the\nMaster of the Sea can't help but get\nswept up in it!
The fate of this beach depends on you,\nso get out there and look alive!
Ma'am, yes, ma'am! But if we're going to\nhave as much fun as possible, we need an\nX-treme Sand Castle Building Spectacular!
And then we're splitting watermelons!\nWith acrobatic somersaults!
Oh, we're barely getting started...\nBehold my beautiful beach bod!\nMesmerizing, isn't it?!
Let's get those beach flags set up!\nI'm ready to run like the wiiiiiind!
Oh ho ho ho! What great fun!\nThis is exactly what I wanted!
Keep going, everyone! Dig deep and\nshow me your most intense merriment!\nYou too, Mikoto!

Hear me, soldiers of the imperial army! 
I, who have attained divine revelation,
will lead you in becoming one with the
greatest of waves!

I cannot remember the last time I
enjoyed myself so. Even my wounds
are healing from my duel with the
surfing warrior.
I am satisfied, humans.\nI wish you all well.
So we won? We saved the beach?\nWe saved everyone's vacations?
The natural order was once in disarray,\nbut no more. The beach is saved.
And WE made contact with the\nMaster of the Sea, which means\nour work is finally done!
Now we can enjoy a real vacation\nwithout anything hanging over us!
Aw, you guys... *sniff*\nI'm so happy for you.
Are all the soldiers deployed to Lathom\nBeach present and accounted for?
C-Commander? What are you\ndoing here, sir?
I have an urgent mission for all of you.\nYou are to track down Codename\nEsmeralda, who has fled Lathom Beach.
We cannot ignore the atrocities Esmeralda\nhas committed. Now all of you, follow me!
B-but sir, we only just completed\nour previous mission.
What mission? Cavorting on the beach\nwith nary a push-up in sight? Bah!\nConsider your leave canceled, soldier!
Now get moving before I have you\nthrown in the stockade!
Well, that's a rather lousy ending.

What Heaven knows, the earth knowsâ€”
and what the earth knows, Mikoto knows.
Our behavior is always being watched,
and this is the result.
This all began with them trying to steal the\nvacations of others. Now, the natural order\nhas deemed fit to return the favor.
Karma is a wheel. It has been ever so.
I guess evil deeds don't pay.
Few things elude the gaze of Heaven.\nBoth your actions and those of the\nsoldiers have surely not escaped its notice.
One day, on some distant beach,\nwe will meet them again and the\nnatural order will shift once more.
And ON that thought, we should probably\nbe getting back to His Highness!
I will accompany you so long\nas Heaven wills it.
After all, our vacation has only begun.
